Items.description:
Sebastian Janikowski made field goals of 50, 51 and 24 yards
Sunday night, lifting the Oakland Raiders past the Philadelphia
Eagles 16-10 in the Hall of Fame game to open the NFL preseason.
Donovan McNabb was 7-9 for 78 yards and a touchdown as the Philadelphia Eagles improved to 2-0 in the preseason with a 20-7 win over the Cleveland Browns.

Indianapolis opened its preseason Thursday with
a successful onside kick by Adam Vinatieri, and Peyton Manning
quickly made the most of his brief appearance by throwing a
touchdown pass in the Colts' 19-17 loss to the St. Louis Rams.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Indianapolis Colts

Items.description:
Rod Marinelli's debut as coach of the Detroit
Lions got off to a good start with a 20-13 win over the Denver
Broncos on Friday night.

Playing in a game for the first time since undergoing a second
major operation on his right shoulder, Chad Pennington worked two series
in the New York Jets' 16-3 preseason loss to the Tampa Bay Buccaneers.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. New York Jets

Items.description:
Michael Koenen, who handled the punting and kickoff duties last
season, booted four
long field goals Friday night, including a 40-yarder as time expired to lead the Atlanta Falcons past the New England Patriots on Friday night.
Items.vs: Atlanta Falcons vs. New England Patriots

Items.description:
Steve McNair produced a touchdown on his first
series with the Baltimore Ravens, then took a seat as his new team
lost 17-16 on the final play of Friday night's game with the New
York Giants.
Items.vs: Baltimore Ravens vs. New York Giants

Items.description:
Alex Smith passed for 137 yards and led the 49ers to a big early lead
in their 28-14 exhibition victory over the Bears on Friday night.

Kurt Warner threw for two first-half scores and the Cardinals
celebrated the long-awaited unveiling of their $465 million stadium
with a 21-13 preseason victory over the Super Bowl champs in front
of a capacity crowd of 63,400.

Keyshawn Johnson, in his first game with Carolina, caught an 18-yard pass
from Jake Delhomme on the first play from scrimmage, the beginning
of a game-opening touchdown drive on the way to a 14-13 win over
the Buffalo Bills on Saturday night.

Daunte Culpepper settled for one 2-yard completion, while the
Jacksonville Jaguars completed four touchdown passes of 50 yards or
more to beat Miami 31-26 in the exhibition opener for both teams
Saturday night.

Mario Williams, the Houston Texans No. 1 draft pick, assisted on one tackle
Saturday night in a quarter of play in Houston's 24-14 preseason
win over the Kansas City Chiefs.
Items.vs: Houston Texans vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Reggie Bush carried six times for 59 yards as the New Orleans Saints held off Vince Young and the Tennessee Titans 19-16 in a preseason game Saturday night.
Items.vs: Tennessee Titans vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description:
Philip Rivers threw for 169 yards and led the Chargers on
two early scoring drives Saturday night in a 17-3 victory over
Green Bay.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description:
Backup quarterback Tony Romo played the entire game and
completed 19 of 25 passes for 235 yards and one touchdown in the
Cowboys' methodical, 13-3 win over the sloppy Seattle Seahawks on
Saturday night.

Washington Redskins running back Clinton Portis partially dislocated his left
shoulder Sunday night during a 19-3 loss to the Cincinnati Bengals.

Moss had one catch for 16 yards in his first game at the
Metrodome since the Vikings traded him to Oakland before last
season, and Brooks looked ragged again in the Raiders' 16-13
preseason victory on Monday night.
Eli Manning threw for a touchdown and set up another as the New York Giants shut out the Kansas City Chiefs 17-0 in a preseason game.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Quarterbacks Steve McNair and Kyle Boller shined as the Baltimore Ravens doubled up the Philadelphia Eagles 20-10 in a preseason game.

Chad Johnson got his first touchdown
this preseason in the Bengals' 44-31 victory over the Bills in an NFL preseason game.

Rookie running back Jerome Harrison caught a 31-yard touchdown pass
in the fourth quarter and finished with 107 total yards Friday
night as the Browns rallied for a 20-16 win over the Detroit Lions.

Brian Urlacher returned an interception 64 yards for a touchdown on the game's third play from scrimmage and Rashied Davis took a kickoff 100 yards for another first-quarter TD Friday night to lead the Bears
over the San Diego Chargers 24-3.
Items.vs: Chicago Bears vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description:
Defensive end Mike Rucker returned a fumble 31 yards for a
touchdown in the second quarter as the Carolina Panthers posted a 17-10
victory over the Jacksonville Jaguars.

Daunte Culpepper took another step on his
comeback trail Saturday night, shrugging off the first real hits
he's taken since undergoing knee surgery and helping the Miami
Dolphins to a 13-10 preseason victory over the Tampa Bay
Buccaneers.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Miami Dolphins

Items.description:
The Jets tried again to sort out two of their marquee positions
in Saturday night's 27-14 victory over the Redskins on Saturday night.
Items.vs: Washington Redskins vs. New York Jets

Items.description:
Brett Favre led the Packers on their first two touchdown drives of the
preseason in the first half, and Green Bay beat the Falcons 38-10
one week after being held to a field goal in San Diego.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Atlanta Falcons

Items.description:
Mario Williams, who made a negligible impact in his professional debut
last week, got the attention of the St. Louis Rams' offensive line
in the Houston Texans' 27-20 win on Saturday night.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Houston Texans

Items.description:
Matt Leinart spent much of Arizona's 30-3 loss to New England
looking like what he is -- a rookie with almost no real practice
experience behind him.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Arizona Cardinals

Items.description:
Ben Roethlisberger, a surprise starter because of his right
thumb injury, threw for a touchdown on the Steelers' opening drive in a 17-10 loss to the Vikings.

Mike Bell atoned for his rookie mistake by scoring
two touchdowns in the Denver Broncos' 35-10 rout of the Tennessee Titans on Friday night.
Peyton Manning was nearly perfect in the first quarter. Seattle made sure the Colts' backups weren't even close the rest of the game.
Aaron Brooks threw a TD pass to Doug Gabriel on Oakland's opening drive, and Andrew Walter led two second-half scoring drives to lead the Raiders to a 23-7 victory.

Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Dallas Cowboys

Items.description: DeAngelo Williams may not start at running back as a rookie, but he likely secured the Carolina Panthers' kickoff return job on Thursday. Williams returned a kick 98 yards for a touchdown in Carolina's 19-10 win over the Miami Dolphins.

Fred Smoot highlighted a big night by Minnesota's defense with a
69-yard interception return for a touchdown as the Vikings blanked
Baltimore's first team offense and beat the Ravens 30-7 on Friday.

While Eli Manning struggled, the defense put in another stellar
performance, notching five sacks and three turnovers in the Giants' 13-7
victory over the New York Jets on Friday night.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. New York Giants

Items.description:
Matt Leinart took over for Kurt Warner in the second quarter and
completed 15-of-21 passes for 144 yards and a touchdown to lead the
Arizona Cardinals over the Chicago Bears 23-16 on Friday night.

Akers kicked field goals of 40, 49 and 52 yards and Jeff Garcia
connected with Greg Lewis on a 61-yard touchdown pass to lead the
Philadelphia Eagles over the Pittsburgh Steelers 16-7 on Friday
night.

Randy Moss caught two touchdown passes from Aaron Brooks and the Oakland
Raiders opened the preseason with four straight wins for the first
time since 1975, beating the Detroit Lions 21-3 Friday night.

Peerless Price went deep, catching a 56-yard touchdown, but it wasn't enough as the Browns won 20-17 Saturday night when Jeff Chandler
hit a 35-yard field goal as time ran out.

Peyton Manning delighted a crowd of 58,228 in a state where
his family holds royalty status, picking apart the New Orleans
defense during three early scoring drives to lead the Indianapolis
Colts to a 27-14 victory over the Saints on Saturday night.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Indianapolis Colts

Items.description:
Terry Glenn made a spectacular touchdown catch for the second straight
game and hauled in a 52-yard pass in double coverage to set up
another score, and the defense took care of the rest in a 17-7
victory over the San Francisco 49ers on Saturday night.

Tom Brady completed 17 of 30 passes for 231 yards and a touchdown to
Benjamin Watson and led the Patriots to five scores on seven
possessions as New England rolled to a 41-0 win over Washington on Saturday night.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Washington Redskins

Items.description:
Byron Leftwich threw a touchdown pass and ran for a score -- both
against backups in the third quarter -- and the Jaguars rallied to
beat the Buccaneers 29-18 in a preseason game Saturday night.
Items.vs: Jacksonville Jaguars vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description:
Jerious Norwood replaced Warrick Dunn on the
third series, then scored a 62-yard touchdown on his second carry
Saturday night in helping the Falcons beat the Tennessee Titans
20-6 Saturday night.

Trent Green directed two scoring drives
and the Kansas City Chiefs snapped an eight-game preseason losing
streak Saturday night with a lackluster 16-12 victory over St.
Louis.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description:
Philip Rivers had a forgettable third
exhibition game, fumbling three times and slightly bruising his
throwing shoulder in the San Diego Chargers' 31-20 victory over the
defending NFC champion Seattle Seahawks on Saturday night.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Seattle Seahawks

Items.description:
The Broncos beat Houston 17-14 Sunday night, spoiling the return
of Texans' first-year coach Gary Kubiak, who spent nearly two decades in
Denver, first as John Elway's backup and then as offensive
coordinator.

With a brace protecting his rebuilt knee, Bengals
quarterback Carson Palmer threw three
touchdown passes Monday night in his first game back from 
injury as Cincinnati crushed Green Bay 48-17.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Bengals vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description:
The New York Giants gave coach Tom
Coughlin a perfect 60th birthday present against the New England
Patriots on Thursday, putting the finishing touches on an
undefeated preseason.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. New England Patriots

Items.description:
John Kasay kicked his fifth field goal on the
final play of the game, a 29-yarder that finished an unbeaten
Carolina preseason and a winless one for Super Bowl champion
Pittsburgh as the Panthers won 15-13 Thursday night.

Charles Sharon caught a pair of touchdown passes and the Jacksonville Jaguars
defeated the Atlanta Falcons 20-17 Thursday night.

On a night when backups got a final shot to show their worth
before 53-man rosters are set Saturday, Marcus Vick and Cleo Lemon helped the
Miami Dolphins beat the Rams 29-9 on Thursday in the preseason
finale for both teams.
Items.vs: Miami Dolphins vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description:
J.P. Losman completed all five of his pass attempts and Willis McGahee
scored on a 1-yard run, helping the Buffalo Bills beat the Detroit
Lions 20-13 Thursday night in the exhibition finale for both teams.

Terrell Owens received a standing ovation
the first time he stepped on the field for the Dallas Cowboys and drew more cheers for catching his first pass. But the biggest surprise was the final score: a 10-10 tie with
the Minnesota Vikings.

The Houston Texans beat the Buccaneers 16-13 Thursday night in a
game where almost all starters on both teams sat out.
Items.vs: Houston Texans vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description:
Steve McNair hit Mark Clayton for a
15-yard touchdown Thursday night for one of the few highlights in
Baltimore's 17-10 victory over Washington.

Rex Grossman threw a 6-yard touchdown pass to tight end Desmond
Clark -- the first TD by Chicago's first-team offense in the
preseason -- to lead the Bears to a 20-7 exhibition win over the
Cleveland Browns on Thursday night.

McKenzie Smith scored on a 1-yard plunge
in the fourth quarter and the Kansas City Chiefs beat the New Orleans Saints 10-9 in a game played almost entirely by reservesThursday night.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description:
A shoulder injury to Arizona's Matt
Leinart dampened a showdown between two of the NFL's quarterbacks
of the future in Denver's 29-23 preseason victory over the
Cardinals on Thursday night.
The defending NFC champion Seattle Seahawks throttled the Oakland Raiders 30-7 in a preseason finale Thursday night.

ookie quarterback Vince Young showed
poise in his first preseason start, consistently turning third
downs into first downs in the Tennessee Titans' 35-21 victory over
the Green Bay Packers on Friday afternoon.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Tennessee Titans

Items.description:
Carson Palmer and Chad Johnson hooked up for three completions Friday night, Rudi Johnson
ran for 45 yards and Chris Henry caught a 14-yard touchdown pass
before the Bengals pulled their starters in a 20-3 victory over the
Indianapolis Colts.

Two days after being re-signed by Philadelphia, A.J. Feeley led the Eagles on three straight scoring drives, but his teammates couldn't hold the lead in a 20-17 loss to the New York Jets in the teams' exhibition finale Friday night.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Philadelphia Eagles

Items.description:
Michael Robinson ran for two touchdowns in the second quarter to help
the San Francisco 49ers end the preseason with a 23-14 victory
Friday night over a San Diego Chargers team still searching for a
backup quarterback.
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: Charlie Batch threw three touchdown passes and Joey Porter returned an interception for a score as the Pittsburgh Steelers won the season opener 28-17 over the Miami Dolphins.
Chad Pennington, returning from two shoulder surgeries in as many years, threw for 319 yards and two touchdowns to lead the Jets to a 23-16 victory over the Titans.
Items.vs: Tennessee Titans vs. New York Jets

Items.description: John Abraham had two sacks and forced two fumbles in his first game with the Falcons, while Michael Vick threw two touchdown passes as Atlanta beat the Panthers 20-6.
Reggie Bush didn't dazzle but certainly didn't disappoint in his NFL debut. He and Drew Brees led the rebuilt Saints to a season-opening 19-14 win over the Browns.
Items.vs: Cleveland Browns vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Chris McAlister returned one of the Ravens' three interceptions 61 yards for a touchdown and 340-pound rookie Haloti Ngata lumbered 60 yards with a tipped pass to set up a field goal to key a 27-0 rout of the Bucs.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Baltimore Ravens

Items.description: Donovan McNabb threw for 314 yards and three touchdowns, including one to Donte' Stallworth, to lead the Eagles to a 24-10 win over the Texans.

Exactly eight months to the day after doctors rebuilt his mangled left knee, Carson Palmer hit nine straight passes in one impressive stretch in Cincinnati's 23-10 victory over K.C., which lost quarterback Trent Green to injury.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Cincinnati Bengals

Items.description: New England showed poise after an ugly start, going ahead on a fourth-quarter safety to beat the Bills 19-17.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Buffalo Bills

Items.description: The Rams' aggressive schemes helped force five turnovers in an 18-10 victory over the Broncos, clinched when Denver quarterback Jake Plummer threw his third interception.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Denver Broncos

Items.description: The defending NFC champions got off on the right foot when Josh Brown kicked a 42-yard field on the last play of the game to lift the Seahawks to a 9-6 win over the Lions.
The Bears barely let Brett Favre touch the ball, shutting out the three-time MVP for the first time in his career in a 26-0 victory over the Packers.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. Chicago Bears

Items.description: Byron Leftwich threw a touchdown pass and ran for a score and Fred Taylor had 115 combined yards to help the Jags beat the Cowboys 24-17, spoiling Terrell Owens' much-anticipated Dallas debut.
Kurt Warner completed 23-of-37 passes for 301 yards and three scores, the Cardinals turned two first-quarter San Francisco turnovers into touchdowns and Arizona held on to beat the 49ers 34-27.

Big brother Peyton was 25-of-41 for 276 yards and a touchdown and the Colts scored on five of their first seven possessions to defeat Eli and the Giants 26-21 in the much-hyped nationally televised matchup of the sons of Archie Manning at Giants Stadium.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Indianapolis Colts

Items.description: Brad Johnson led a 54-yard fourth-quarter drive, capped by Ryan Longwell's 31-yard field goal with one minute remaining, to give the Vikings a 19-16 victory over the Washington Redskins on Monday night.

With LaDainian Tomlinson running through the Oakland defense and Shawn Merriman harassing Aaron Brooks, it
didn't appear to matter who played quarterback for San Diego.
Items.vs: Oakland Raiders vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: The Cincinnati Bengals beat the Cleveland Browns 34-17 on Sunday despite losing three starters to injury -- a troubling turn for the defending AFC North champs.
Eli Manning brought the Giants back from a 17-point deficit in the fourth quarter and threw a 31-yard TD pass to Plaxico Burress with 3:11 left in OT for a 30-24 win over the Eagles.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Eagles vs. New York Giants

Items.description: Even with an injury-depleted defense, Buffalo ruined Daunte Culpepper's first home game before his new fans with surprising ease.

The Ravens forced six turnovers, got a safety from Adalius
Thomas and kept the Raiders out of the end zone Sunday in a 28-6 victory.

Peyton Manning and the Indianapolis Colts played a near-perfect game Sunday. The Houston Texans and David
Carr looked like, well, their old selves.
Ryan Longwell's 16-yard touchdown pass to Richard Owens on a fake kick tied the game in the fourth quarter, and his third field goal gave the Vikings a 16-13 overtime win.
Led by Michael Vick and Warrick Dunn, the Atlanta Falcons took their running game to a whole new level.
Items.vs: Atlanta Falcons vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: Drew Brees overcame three early turnovers by throwing for 353 yards, leading the Saints to a 34-27 victory over the Green Bay Packers on Sunday.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Rex Grossman had his best game as a pro, and the Chicago Bears' defense silenced Detroit's Roy Williams and the Lions.
Antonio Bryant caught a 72-yard touchdown pass from Alex Smith, and San Francisco's defense stood strong in the final minutes for a 20-13 win over the Rams.
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: Seattle got touchdowns from Shaun Alexander and Darrell Jackson on its first two drives before blown opportunities by the Cardinals led to an underwhelming 21-10 win.
Jake Plummer led Denver to a 9-6 win over Kansas City on Jason Elam's 39-yard field goal 5:10 into overtime Sunday.
Items.vs: Denver Broncos vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: The student gave the teacher a scare, but Bill Belichick's Patriots held off a late rally by Eric Mangini's Jets for a 24-17 victory Sunday.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: Six days after blanking the Raiders, the Chargers came within 3:09 of consecutive shutouts for the first time in club history in a 40-7 rout of the Titans on Sunday.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Tennessee Titans

Items.description:
While Terrell Owens botched his home debut with drops and
penalties, Terry Glenn set up Dallas' first two TDs, then scored a third with a 40-yard catch in the Cowboys' 27-10 win.

The Jaguars harassed Ben Roethlisberger, held Willie Parker to 20 yards on 11 carries and ended the defending Super Bowl champions' nine-game winning streak with a 9-0 victory --  the lowest-scoring game in Monday Night Football history.
The Chicago Bears and their defense are still in charge of the NFC North for now.
Carson Palmer threw two touchdown passes to T.J. Houshmandzadeh less than a minute apart, and the Bengals rallied for a 28-20 victory over the Steelers.
Mark Brunell kept connecting, pass after pass. By the time he was through with the Texans' shaky defense, he set an NFL record and gave the Redskins their first win.
Quarterback Chad Pennington and an opportunistic defense made up for the Jets' lack of a running game in a win over the Bills.
Items.vs: Buffalo Bills vs. New York Jets

Items.description: Jacksonville held Peyton Manning to one touchdown pass, but Indianapolis found other ways to score in a 21-14 victory Sunday.

Brett Favre joined elite company with the 400th touchdown pass of his career, then added a two more scores to lead
the Packers to their first win, 31-24 over the Lions.
Items.vs: Detroit Lions vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: A 50-yard drive set up a 39-yard field goal by Olindo Mare with 3:39 left to help sputtering Miami beat the hapless Titans 13-10 on Sunday.
Jake Delhomme led a last-minute drive that produced John Kasay's fourth long field goal of the day with 2 seconds left, giving the Panthers a 26-24 win over the Bucs.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Carolina Panthers

Items.description: Matt Stover kicked the Ravens to their first 3-0 start since football returned to Baltimore.
Seattle's Matt Hasselbeck threw five TD passes, and Eli Manning had three interceptions as the Giants were way behind early and never caught up in a 42-30 loss Sunday.
Items.vs: Seattle Seahawks vs. New York Giants

Items.description: Kurt Warner, who threw three interceptions, fumbled a snap at the Rams 18 with 1:46 to play, and Will Witherspoon recovered to allow St. Louis to hold on to beat Arizona 16-14 Sunday.
Items.vs: Arizona Cardinals vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: Brian Westbrook rushed for 117 yards and two ouchdowns, also catching a scoring pass from Donovan McNabb in the Eagles' 38-24 victory over the 49ers on Sunday.
Jake Plummer threw touchdown passes of 83 and 32 yards to Javon Walker on Sunday night as the Broncos beat New England 17-7.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Denver Broncos

Items.description:
In an earsplitting return to their rebuilt stadium, the Saints
gave the Big Easy something to cheer about -- an undefeated football
team that made it look easy with a 23-3 victory over the Atlanta
Falcons on Monday night.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Atlanta Falcons

Items.description: Damon Huard played almost flawlessly in a 41-0 rout of San Francisco while Kansas City seized a 24-0 halftime lead en route to its first shutout in almost four years.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. San Francisco 49ers

Items.description: Steve McNair brought the unbeaten Ravens back for the second week in a row, throwing a 10-yard pass to Todd Heap with 34 seconds left to beat San Diego 16-13.
Items.vs: Baltimore Ravens vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description: In a game that featured the return of T.O. and the first NFL start for Vince Young, Drew Bledsoe and Terry Glenn hooked up on two 13-yard TD passes and Dallas beat the Titans 45-14.
Jake Delhomme threw a 4-yard TD pass to Drew Carter midway through the fourth quarter to put Carolina ahead to stay as the Panthers handed New Orleans its first loss, 21-18.
Items.vs: Carolina Panthers vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: DeAngelo Hall returned an interception 36 yards for a score, Jerious Norwood broke off a 78-yard scoring run and Morten Andersen kicked five field goals in Atlanta's 32-10 win.
After Justin Miller's 103-yard dash gave the Jets the lead with 2:20 left, Peyton Manning led Indianapolis on another winning drive in a wild 31-28 victory Sunday.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Indianapolis Colts

Items.description: J.P. Losman passed for 222 yards and a touchdown and set up another score with a 15-yard scramble, and Buffalo held off Minnesota 17-12.
Mario Williams finally got a sack, and the Houston Texans picked up their first win.

In a shootout befitting Mike Martz's return to St. Louis, Isaac
Bruce caught a 5-yard touchdown pass with 1:56 to play as the Rams rallied to beat Detroit 41-34 on Sunday.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Detroit Lions

Items.description: Santana Moss leaped between two defenders to catch a 68-yard touchdown pass 1:49 into overtime Sunday giving the Redskins a 36-30 victory over the Jaguars.
Charlie Frye threw three touchdown passes and Cleveland used three long returns to rally from an early 18-point deficit and beat the Raiders 24-21 on Sunday.
Laurence Maroney ran for 125 yards and two touchdowns Sunday, restoring balance to the Patriots' offense and setting up a 38-13 victory over the Bengals.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Bengals vs. New England Patriots

Items.description:
The Bears showed how serious they are about contending for the NFC title, dominating the defending
conference champion Seahawks 37-6 on Sunday night.
Donovan McNabb had a huge game in the Eagles' 31-9 rout of the Packers on Monday night.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Eagles vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: Julius Peppers had a sack, forced a fumble and hit quarterback Charlie Frye five other times, and the Panthers beat Cleveland 20-12 on Sunday.
Peyton Manning hooked up with Reggie Wayne for a 2-yard touchdown pass with 5:10 left and giving Indianapolis a 14-13 come-from-behind victory over Tennessee.

Detroit squandered a 17-3 lead in the fourth quarter and the
Vikings defense scored two touchdowns off turnovers by Jon Kitna in the fourth for a 26-17 victory Sunday.
Rex Grossman threw two touchdown passes, Cedric Benson scored his first two NFL touchdowns, and the Bears forced five turnovers in a 40-7 drubbing of the Bills.
Brett Favre couldn't deliver another fourth-quarter comeback in the Packers' 23-20 loss to the Rams on Sunday.
Items.vs: Green Bay Packers vs. St. Louis Rams

Items.description: Asante Samuel intercepted two passes by Joey Harrington that led to two touchdowns, and New England overcame a mediocre performance by Tom Brady to beat Miami 20-10.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. Miami Dolphins

Items.description: Reggie Bush returned a punt 65 yards for his first NFL touchdown with less than five minutes left to lift New Orleans to a 24-21 victory over Tampa Bay on Sunday.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers

Items.description: Michael Strahan and the much-maligned Giants defense limited Washington to 164 total yards, and Eli Manning threw a touchdown pass in a 19-3 victory.
Items.vs: New York Giants vs. Washington Redskins

Items.description: Arnaz Battle caught two touchdown passes from Alex Smith, and the 49ers overcame Randy Moss' 100th career TD reception for a 34-20 victory over winless Oakland.

The Jaguars scored touchdowns on four of their first five
possessions, quickly rebounding from consecutive losses and beating the New York Jets 41-0 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Jacksonville Jaguars vs. New York Jets

Items.description: Matt Leinart's first NFL game as a starter Sunday had a great beginning, a so-so middle and a nearly fantastic finish, but the Cardinals lost to the Chiefs 23-20.
Items.vs: Arizona Cardinals vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Donovan McNabb threw two long touchdown passes, and Lito Sheppard returned an interception 102 yards in the final minute to seal the Eagles' 38-24 victory over Dallas.
Philip Rivers threw two touchdown passes, including a 22-yarder to Antonio Gates in the third quarter that lifted San Diego to a 23-13 win over Pittsburgh.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Pittsburgh Steelers

Items.description: In a game of tough defenses and bad weather, the Broncos did enough to beat the Ravens 13-3 on Monday night.

Josh Brown's 54-yard field goal as time expired
Sunday gave the Seattle Seahawks a 30-28 win over St. Louis,
spoiling the Rams' chance for a third fumble-induced win of the
season.
Items.vs: St. Louis Rams vs. Seattle Seahawks

Items.description:
Vince Young has his first NFL victory, with
big assists from a Tennessee Titans running back, a kicker and a
tight end who blocked a punt.

John Carney kicked a
31-yard field goal as time expired to lift the Saints to a 27-24
victory over the Philadelphia Eagles in a matchup of division
leaders.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Philadelphia Eagles

Items.description:
The Carolina Panthers posted a 23-21 victory over the Baltimore
Ravens, who lost quarterback Steve McNair to a concussion.

Michael Clayton's 8-yard dive was a touchdown -- barely -- lifting the
previously winless Bucs to a 14-13 victory over the Cincinnati
Bengals with 35 seconds remaining Sunday.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Cincinnati Bengals

Items.description:
Terrell Owens caught three touchdown passes as the Cowboys scored 31
unanswered points in the second half en route to a comfortable
34-6 victory over the Houston Texans.

Roy Williams had 10 receptions for 161 yards -- both career highs
-- and scored a touchdown while Kevin Jones ran for a season-high
127 yards and a score to lead the Lions to a 20-17 win over the
Buffalo Bills on Sunday.

Tiki Barber outplayed the NFL's best ground team by running for 185
yards, Jeremy Shockey caught a couple of touchdown passes and the
New York Giants rallied past the Falcons in the second half for a
27-14 victory Sunday.
Items.vs: Atlanta Falcons vs. New York Giants

Items.description:
Laveranues Coles caught two touchdown passes and Mike Nugent kicked a pair of 33-yard field goals, and the Jets barely held on for a
20-17 win against the Dolphins on Sunday.
Items.vs: New York Jets vs. Miami Dolphins

Items.description: SAN DIEGO 48, SAN FRANCISCO 19
Items.vs: San Francisco 49ers vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description:
The Steelers revived everything they displayed in winning the
championship as Ben Roethlisberger threw his first two touchdown
passes since the AFC championship game in a 45-7 rout of the Chiefs
on Sunday.
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Steelers vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description:
Jason Elam kicked two field goals, Tatum Bell ran for a short
touchdown and Champ Bailey picked off another key pass as the
Broncos defeated the winless Oakland Raiders 13-3 Sunday night.

Chicago, down 20-0 at the half, returned two fumbles for
touchdowns, then Devin Hester returned a punt 83 yards for a
touchdown with 2:58 remaining and the Bears (6-0) overcame six
turnovers by Rex Grossman to beat the Cardinals 24-23 Monday night.

Matt Bryant gave the Tampa Bay 
Buccaneers an improbable win while sending the Philadelphia
Eagles to an agonizing loss with one of the most amazing kicks
in NFL history.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Buccaneers vs. Philadelphia Eagles

Items.description:
Lawrence Tynes hit a career-long 53-yard field goal with 6
seconds left, atoning for a first-quarter miss and giving the
Kansas City Chiefs a 30-27 victory over the Chargers on Sunday.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. San Diego Chargers

Items.description:
Carson Palmer finally mastered the wind and led a fourth-quarter drive
Sunday that culminated in his 1-yard throw to T.J. Houshmandzadeh,
giving Cincinnati to a 17-14 victory over the Carolina Panthers.

Ranked last in the NFL in pass defense, Green Bay intercepted
Joey Harrington three times and beat the woeful Dolphins 34-24
Sunday.
Items.vs: Miami Dolphins vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description:
David Carr passed for 224 yards and two touchdowns as the lowly
Houston Texans rolled to a 27-7 triumph over the Jaguars.

Corey Dillon's two touchdowns rushing in the first half gave the

Items.description:
Done in by repeated mistakes from Tony Romo and a few more by
Terence Newman, the Cowboys blew their last chance to win the NFC
East with a 39-31 loss to the Lions on Sunday.

Larry Johnson rushed for 138 yards on 33 carries Sunday in
Kansas City's 35-30 victory over Jacksonville, giving him an
NFL-record 416 carries this season.
Items.vs: Kansas City Chiefs vs. Jacksonville Jaguars

Items.description:
Using a stellar performance from the defense and an efficient
effort from the offense, the Ravens beat the Buffalo Bills 19-7
Sunday to earn the No. 2 seed in the AFC and a first-round bye in
the playoffs.

Philip Rivers threw two touchdown passes after injuring his right foot,
and LaDainian Tomlinson also limped off after wrapping up his first
NFL rushing title in leading the Chargers to a 27-20 win over the
Arizona Cardinals on Sunday.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. Arizona Cardinals

Items.description:
Joe Nedney kicked a 36-yard field goal with 1:56 left in overtime as
the Niners eliminated Denver from the playoffs with a stunning
26-23 victory Sunday.

Peyton Manning threw two touchdowns, ran for another and watched his
maligned defense limit Miami to five field goals before giving up a
late touchdown, and the Colts held on for a 27-22 victory.

Thanks to the Detroit Lions, Jeff Garcia and the rest of
Philadelphia's starters rested up for the playoffs while the
backups finished off a remarkable late-season run with a 24-17
victory over Atlanta on Sunday.
Brett Favre showed he still has some ammo left in that gunslinging right arm, passing for 285 yards to lead the Green Bay Packers to a 26-7 victory over the Bears on Sunday night.
Items.vs: Chicago Bears vs. Green Bay Packers

Items.description: While Peyton Manning's numbers were good, his performance was mediocre. Fortunately for the Colts, their defense bailed them out in a 23-8 victory over the inept Kansas City Chiefs.
Items.vs: Indianapolis Colts vs. Kansas City Chiefs

Items.description: Tony Romo's botched hold on a 19-yard field goal try with 1:19 left forced the Pro Bowl quarterback to scramble left, but he was tackled at the 2 and the Seahawks escaped with a 21-20 victory in the wildest of wild-card games Saturday night.

Tom Brady capped long drives with short touchdown passes to Daniel Graham and Kevin Faulk, and Asante Samuel sealed it with a 36-yard interception return for a score with 4:54 left in the game as the New England Patriots beat the New York Jets 37-16.
Items.vs: New England Patriots vs. New York Jets

Items.description: David Akers hit a 38-yard field goal with no time remaining to give the Philadelphia Eagles a 23-20 victory over the New York Giants in a wild-card playoff game on Sunday.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Eagles vs. New York Giants

Items.description: Vinatieri kicked five field goals Saturday to put his name in the NFL record book and carry Indianapolis past the Baltimore Ravens 15-6 and into the AFC Championship game.
Deuce McAllister and rookie sensation Reggie Bush led the Saints past the Philadelphia Eagles 27-24 Saturday and into the NFC Championship Game.
Items.vs: New Orleans Saints vs. Philadelphia Eagles

Items.description:
Robbie Gould kicked the Chicago Bears into
the NFC Championship Game for the first time in 18 years.

Tom Brady and the New England Patriots shocked league MVP LaDainian
Tomlinson and the San Diego Chargers on Sunday, winning 24-21 to
move within one win of their fourth Super Bowl trip in six seasons.
Items.vs: San Diego Chargers vs. New England Patriots

Items.description:
After romping past the
New Orleans Saints 39-14 on Sunday, the Bears are headed to their first
NFL title game since the 1985 team overwhelmed the league and
shuffled in under Mike Ditka and Jim McMahon.
Items.vs: Chicago Bears vs. New Orleans Saints

Items.description: Peyton Manning finally won the big one, leading the Colts past the Patriots 38-34 on Sunday in the AFC Championship Game.
Items.vs: Indianapolis Colts vs. New England Patriots

Items.description: Chicago's Devin Hester returned the opening kick of Super Bowl XLI for a touchdown, but Indianapolis bounced back to win 29-17.

The 2007 Pro Bowl was the National Football League's all-star game for the 2006 season. The game took place on February 10, 2007, at Aloha Stadium in Honolulu, Hawaii. The game was held on a Saturday instead of the usual Sunday after the Super Bowl because of a request by broadcaster CBS.
The 2007 Pro Bowl marked the 28th consecutive time that the National Football League's all-star game was held in Honolulu. The NFC was coached by Sean Payton of the New Orleans Saints. The AFC was coached by Bill Belichick of the New England Patriots.
